# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Deploy-branch hygiene
#
# Paths listed below MUST NOT live on deploy/* branches. They are dev-reference
# only and live on develop-test / develop-stable / main. Hard enforcement is
# done by .github/workflows/protect-deploy-branch.yml — this file is the soft
# layer: when a merge from a dev branch tries to bring these paths back, git
# uses the "ours" merge driver to keep the deploy-branch version (i.e. nothing).
#
# To activate locally, run once per machine:
#   git config --global merge.ours.driver true
#
# Why this exists: see docs/DEPLOY_BRANCH_GUIDE.md
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Backend code — deployed via `supabase functions deploy` and `supabase db push`,
# not via this Docker pipeline. Repo copy lives on develop-test for reference.
supabase/**                                            merge=ours

# Dev-only tooling
scripts/**                                             merge=ours

# Unused CI config (we use GitHub Actions, not Azure DevOps)
azure-pipelines.yml                                    merge=ours

# Dev-reference docs (architecture, ADRs, release notes, etc.)
docs/architecture/**                                   merge=ours
docs/adr/**                                            merge=ours
docs/reference/**                                      merge=ours
docs/releases/**                                       merge=ours
docs/workflows/**                                      merge=ours
docs/CONTRIBUTING.md                                   merge=ours
docs/DATABASE_SCHEMA.md                                merge=ours
docs/DISPATCH_EMAIL_SYSTEM.md                          merge=ours
docs/GRBAC_SYSTEM.md                                   merge=ours
docs/MIGRATION_NOTES.md                                merge=ours
docs/MODULE_OVERVIEW.md                                merge=ours
docs/SCHEMA_MIGRATION_item_code_to_part_number.md      merge=ours
docs/architecture.md                                   merge=ours
